# Count via fold: how many elements equal a target.
*count_eq(xs as Vec of i64, target as i64) returns i64
    n is 0
    i is 0
    while i < xs.length
        if xs.get(i) equals target
            n is n + 1
        i is i + 1
    n

*main
    xs is vec()
    xs.push(1)
    xs.push(2)
    xs.push(2)
    xs.push(3)
    xs.push(2)
    xs.push(4)
    log count_eq(xs, 2)
    log count_eq(xs, 9)
